%2C%20detailing%20events%20that%20took%20place%20on%20October%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20October%204%2C%20the%20plane%20departed%20from%20London's%20Stansted%20Airport%20for%20Orlando%20International%20Airport.%20It%20was%20carrying%20three%20pilots%2C%20an%20engineer%2C%20a%20loadmaster%2C%20six%20cabin%20crew%2C%20as%20well%20as%20nine%20passengers%2C%20and%20was%20scheduled%20for%20a%20multi-day%20charter%2C%20the%20bulletin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20shortly%20after%20takeoff%2C%20several%20passengers%20noticed%20that%20the%20aircraft%20cabin%20seemed%20both%20colder%20and%20noisier%20than%20usual%2C%20according%20to%20the%20bulletin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plane%20continued%20to%20climb%20to%20an%20altitude%20of%2010%2C000%20feet%20and%20the%20seatbelt%20signs%20were%20switched%20off%2C%20according%20to%20the%20bulletin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20at%20this%20point%20that%20the%20loadmaster%20walked%20toward%20the%20back%20of%20the%20plane%20and%20noticed%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20cabin%20noise%2C%20it%20said%2C%20with%20the%20noise%20%26quot%3Bloud%20enough%20to%20damage%20your%20hearing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20loadmaster%20also%20noticed%20that%20the%20window%20seal%20on%20a%20window%20on%20the%20left%20side%20of%20the%20plane%20was%20%26quot%3Bflapping%20in%20the%20airflow%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bulletin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20flight%20crew%20decided%20to%20stop%20the%20plane's%20climb%20at%2014%2C000%20feet%20and%20reduce%20airspeed%2C%20despite%20no%20%26quot%3Babnormal%20indications%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20flight%20deck%20and%20normal%20operations%20of%20the%20aircraft's%20pressurization%20system%2C%20per%20the%20bulletin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20engineer%20and%20a%20pilot%20were%20then%20dispatched%20to%20take%20a%20look%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20agreed%20that%20the%20aircraft%20should%20return%20to%20Stansted%2C%20and%20the%20plane%20landed%2036%20minutes%20after%20taking%20off%2C%20the%20bulletin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20parked%2C%20the%20cabin%20crew%20inspected%20the%20plane%20and%20discovered%20that%20two%20window%20assemblies%20%E2%80%94%20the%20inner%20and%20outer%20panes%20and%20rubber%20seal%20%E2%80%94%20were%20missing%2C%20the%20bulletin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Ftravel%2Fnews-and-advice%2Fplane-stansted-airport-missing-windows-accident-takeoff-b2443042.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20The%20Independent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20only%20thing%20in%20place%20was%20the%20scratch%20pane%2C%20a%20piece%20of%20plastic%20that%20prevents%20passengers%20from%20touching%20the%20outer%20window.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inner%20pane%20and%20seal%20from%20a%20third%20window%20had%20also%20been%20displaced%2C%20the%20AAIB%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20the%20day%20before%20the%20flight%2C%20the%20plane%20had%20been%20used%20during%20a%20filming%20event%20where%20high-power%20lights%20were%20active%20for%20up%20to%20five-and-a-half%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThermal%20damage%20and%20window%20deformation%20were%20subsequently%20observed%20in%20the%20area%20around%20the%20overwing%20emergency%20exit%2C%20which%20the%20AAIB%20attributed%20to%20extended%20exposure%20to%20elevated%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AAIB%20said%20in%20the%20bulletin%20that%20the%20incident%20could%20have%20had%20far%20%26quot%3Bmore%20serious%26quot%3B%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhereas%20in%20this%20case%20the%20damage%20became%20apparent%20at%20around%20FL100%20%5B10%2C000%20feet%5D%20and%20the%20flight%20was%20concluded%20uneventfully%2C%20a%20different%20level%20of%20damage%20by%20the%20same%20means%20might%20have%20resulted%20in%20more%20serious%20consequences%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20now%20working%20with%20the%20plane's%20manufacturer%20and%20operator%20to%20fully%20understand%20the%20properties%20of%20the%20lights%20used%2C%20and%20how%20to%20mitigate%20risks%20in%2