20have%20connections%20with%20the%20ruling%20or%20opposition%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kaul%20also%20held%20that%20the%20expertise%20of%20a%20criminal%20lawyer%20who%20has%20defended%20people%20against%20the%20government%20cannot%20be%20held%20against%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPick-and-choose%20must%20stop%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Kaul%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20recommended%20Delhi%20high%20court%20Chief%20Justice%20Satish%20Chandra%20Sharma%2C%20Rajasthan%20high%20court%20Chief%20Justice%20Augustine%20George%20Masih%20and%20Gauhati%20high%20court%20Chief%20Justice%20Sandeep%20Mehta%20for%20elevation%20as%20Supreme%20Court%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20treatment%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20suggestions%20has%20been%20a%20sustained%20cause%20for%20tussle%20between%20the%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2019%2F35036%2F35036_2019_31_1502_27748_Judgement_20-Apr-2021.pdf%5C%22%3Eruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20was%20obligated%20to%20revert%20to%20the%20collegium%20within%2018%20weeks%20if%20it%20had%20any%20reservation%20to%20a%20name%20proposed%20for%20judgeship.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20has%2C%20since%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpreview%2F679198%5C%22%3E%C2%A0repeatedly%20raised%3C%2Fa%3E%20concerns%20about%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20delays%20in%20deciding%20on%20numerous%20collegium%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699442108000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-collegium-political-connections%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Sanjay%20Kishan%20Kaul%20and%20Justice%20Sudhanshu%20Dhulai%20told%20Attorney%20General%20for%20India%20R.%20Venkataramani%20that%20the%20government%20has%20to%20balance%20the%20fact%20that%2040%25%20of%20states%20are%20governed%20by%20opposition%20parties.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-collegium-political-connections%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We%20moved%20to%20Mexico%20from%20Texas%20and%20have%20never%20been%20happier.%20We're%20saving%20%242%2C000%20a%20month%20and%20can%20even%20afford%20to%20go%20to%20the%20dentist.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22934%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Spencer%20(left)%20and%20Braelyn%20Stone%20(right)%20in%20M%C3%A9rida%2C%20Mexico.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a97e1b788914e5551f54b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22963%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpencer%20(left)%20and%20Braelyn%20Stone%20(right)%20moved%20to%20M%C3%A9rida%2C%20Mexico%20in%202022.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20Stones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBraelyn%20and%20Spencer%20Stone%20moved%20from%20Houston%2C%20Texas%2C%20to%20M%C3%A9rida%2C%20Mexico%2C%20in%202022.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20couple%20chose%20the%20city%20for%20its%20cheaper%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20safety%2C%20and%20healthcare.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey've%20reduced%20their%20debt%20by%20living%20in%20Mexico%20but%20miss%20their%20family%20and%20friends.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20social-media%20managers%20Braelyn%2C%2031%2C%20and%20Spencer%20Stone%2C%2027%2C%20about%20moving%20to%20M%C3%A9rida%2C%20Mexico%2C%20in%202022%20after%20becoming%20unable%20to%20afford%20life%20in%20Houston%2C%20Texas.%20The%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpencer%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20Houston%2C%20we%20basically%20moved%20apartment%20to%20apartment%20due%20to%20pricing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBraelyn%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Before%20leaving%20the%20city%2C%20we%20were%20in%20a%201%2C015-square-foot%20apartment%20that%20was%20about%20seven%20minutes%20from%20downtown.%20Our%20rent%20was%20%241%2C740.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpencer%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20At%20the%20end%20of%20that%20lease%2C%20they%20raised%20the%20renewal%20rate%20by%20%24400%20a%20month.%20There%20was%20no%20way%20we%20could%20do%20that.%20We%20looked%20around%20Houston%20and%20saw%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20apartments%20that%20we%20would%20be%20comfortable%20living%20in%20were%20just%20completely%20financially%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20we%20were%20also%20going%20through%20some%20personal%20things.%20We%20decided%20we%20really%20wanted%20to%20live%20and%20experience%20a%20different%20lifestyle.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20had%20the%20idea%20of%20moving%20to%20Mexico.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBraelyn%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20no%20longer%20felt%20safe%20in%20Houston.%20Our%20car%20had%20been%20vandalized%20three%20times%2C%20credit%20cards%20skimmed%2C%20and%20expensive%20cameras%20stolen.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222672%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Stones%20car%20without%20tires.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a948e36d588dc55cc7a5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221503%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Stones%20car%20that%20was%20broken%20into%20while%20living%20in%20Houston.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20Stones%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20increase%20of%20shootings%20was%20also%20overwhelming%20for%20us.%20The%20fear%20of%20being%20in%20the%20wrong%20place%20at%20the%20wrong%20time%20was%20just%20getting%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOur%20crippling%20debt%20furthered%20our%20decision%20to%20move%20to%20Mexico%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBraelyn%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ELiving%20in%20Houston%20was%20just%20becoming%20financially%20ridiculous.%20The%20city%20is%20huge%2C%20so%20it%20feels%20like%20your%20gas%20gets%20stolen%20just%20getting%20around.%20Groceries%20also%20started%20going%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpencer%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Healthcare%20was%20also%20another%20huge%20reason.%20We%20don't%20have%20medical%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBraelyn%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Spencer%20and%20I%20are%20both%20contract%20workers.%20So%20trying%20to%20pay%20for%20insurance%20on%20top%20of%20everything%20else%20in%20Houston%20wasn't%20really%20doable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224371%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20above%20view%20of%20downtown%20Houston%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a94db36d588dc55cc7b3c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222912%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHouston%2C%20Texas.%3Cp%3EDuy%20Do%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBraelyn%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20When%20combined%2C%20we%20also%20owe%20over%20%24200%2C000%20in%20debt.%20Student%20loans%20are%20by%20far%20the%20largest%20portion%20of%20our%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20Baylor%20for%20one%20year%20and%20realized%20I%20was%20spending%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20on%20a%20degree%20I%20wasn't%20happy%20about.%20So%20I%20transferred%20to%20the%20University%20of%20Houston%20and%20finished%20my%20degree%20with%20a%20BS%20in%20digital%20media.%20I%20have%20%2468%2C000%20in%20student%20loan%20debt%2C%20and%20it's%20rising%20due%20to%20interest.%20Spencer's%20education%20has%20been%20on%20and%20off%20since%202014.%20He%20estimates%20he%20will%20have%20over%20%24100%2C000%20in%20student%20loan%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20student%20loans%2C%20we'd%20be%20looking%20at%20about%20%2417%2C000%20in%20credit%20card%20debt.%20COVID%20hit%20us%20hard%20and%20we%20both%20struggled%20for%20work.%20We%20also%20got%20married%20in%20October%202022.%20Our%20wedding%20was%20close%20to%20%2410%2C000.%20We%20paid%20half%20while%20our%20family%20chipped%20in%20for%20the%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Stones%20kissing%20on%20their%20wedding%20day.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a951cb788914e5551f090%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Stones%20on%20their%20wedding%20day.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20Stones%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBraelyn%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMexico%20just%20made%20more%20sense%20financially%20than%20moving%20anywhere%20else%20locally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20found%20a%20better%20home%20at%20a%20lower%20price%20in%20Mexico%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBraelyn%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20arrived%20in%20Mexico%20in%20November%202022.%20We%20are%20renting%20a%20luxury%20condo%20from%20a%20landlord.%20It%20has%20three%20bedrooms%20and%20two-and-a-half%20baths.%20Our%20building%20is%20gated%20and%20has%20a%20private%20park.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20rent%20comes%20out%20to%20about%20%241%2C230%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rectoria%20El%20Jesus%20Tercera%20Orden%20in%20M%C3%A9rida%2C%20Mexico.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a95913cc84b4dfafe1225%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERectoria%20El%20Jesus%20Tercera%20Orden%20in%20M%C3%A9rida%2C%20Mexico.%3Cp%3EPawel%20Toczynski%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20call%20M%C3%A9rida%20paradise.%20Even%20the%20locals%20that%20live%20here%20call%20it%20%26quot%3Btranquillo%26quot%3B%20which%20means%20peaceful.%20That's%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20we%20moved%20to%20the%20city%20%E2%80%94%20it%20feels%20so%20safe%20and%20you%20feel%20at%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crime%20rate%20in%20M%C3%A9rida%20is%20crazy%20low.%20I%20feel%20safe%20walk